body:
The following simple code result in a crash. Everithing OK when substituting num_error++;  with num_error=num_error+1; 

```
module bug;
timeunit 1ns / 1ps;
logic a,b;
localparam N = 4;
localparam K = 2;
localparam FILENAME = "val1.txt";
logic [K-1:0] dati [1:N];

initial
begin
   int num_error;
   num_error=0;
   $readmemb(FILENAME,dati);
   
   for (int j=1; j<=N; j++)
   begin
      {a,b} = dati[j];
      #1ns;
      assert (a==b) else
         begin
            num_error++;
            $info("Test %2d failed.",j);
         end
   end
   $display("End of simulation. Errors:%2d",num_error);
   $finish;
end
endmodule 
```

/* content of file val1.txt
0_0
0_1
1_0
1_1
*/

Command issued: 
verilator --binary --timing  --assert bug.sv 

Verilator version = Verilator 5.017 devel rev v5.014-143-g2385ab829
OS = Ubuntu 22.04.3
